calls for real leadership.

80
00:05:43,309 --> 00:05:47,109
People, your taxes are high
because of illegal immigrants.

81
00:05:47,213 --> 00:05:49,738
That's right. Illegal immigrants.

82
00:05:49,849 --> 00:05:51,749
We need to get rid of them!

83
00:05:51,851 --> 00:05:55,912
"Immigants. " I knew it was them!

84
00:05:56,022 --> 00:05:58,490
Even when it was the bears,
I knew it was them.

85
00:05:58,591 --> 00:06:02,721
Oh! Won't somebody please
think of the children?

86
00:06:02,829 --> 00:06:05,525
In one week, the town will vote
on a special referendum...

87
00:06:05,631 --> 00:06:09,294
whether or not to deport
all illegal immigrants from Springfield.

88
00:06:09,402 --> 00:06:11,604
It shall be known as Proposition 24. Yea!

89
00:06:11,639 --> 00:06:12,298
It shall be known as Proposition 24. Yea!

90
00:06:20,513 --> 00:06:23,846
Hey, German boy!
Go back to "Germania. "

91
00:06:23,950 --> 00:06:26,976
I do not deserve this!

92
00:06:27,086 --> 00:06:29,987
I've come here legally
as an exchange student.

93
00:06:30,089 --> 00:06:33,684
Young man, the only thing
we exchange for you is our national dignity.

94
00:06:35,862 --> 00:06:39,992
You want to pick on immigrants,
then pick on Willie!

95
00:06:40,099 --> 00:06:43,557
Willie, please! The children
want to pick on someone their own size.

96
00:06:51,377 --> 00:06:54,676
I don't see how you can support
Proposition 24, Dad.

97
00:06:54,781 --> 00:06:56,772
Open your eyes, Lisa.

98
00:06:56,883 --> 00:07:00,751
Our schools are so jam-packed with immigrants,
kids like Bart have lost the will to learn.

99
00:07:00,853 --> 00:07:02,753
There's no denying it, Sis.

100
00:07:02,855 --> 00:07:05,653
But immigration is
what America's all about.

101
00:07:05,758 --> 00:07:09,091
Even the Simpson family immigrated
to America. Right, Grandpa?

102
00:07:09,195 --> 00:07:11,220
Okay, you twisted my arm.

103
00:07:11,330 --> 00:07:15,164
The Simpson story begins
back in the old country.

104
00:07:15,268 --> 00:07:17,498
<i>I forget which one exactly.</i>

105
00:07:17,603 --> 00:07:21,733
<i>My father would drone
on and on about America.</i>

106
00:07:21,841 --> 00:07:24,332
<i>He thought it was the greatest thing
since sliced bread...</i>

107
00:07:24,444 --> 00:07:28,107
<i>sliced bread having been
invented the previous winter.</i>

108
00:07:28,214 --> 00:07:31,206
See this, Son?
That's where we're going to live.

109
00:07:31,317 --> 00:07:34,912
Maybe not today.
Maybe not tomorrow. But someday.

110
00:07:35,021 --> 00:07:37,751
<i>Later that day, we set sail for America.</i>

111
00:07:39,859 --> 00:07:41,759
There it is.
Our new home.

112
00:07:43,062 --> 00:07:44,290
Whee! I love America!

113
00:07:44,397 --> 00:07:45,830
Abe, supper's on!

114
00:07:45,932 --> 00:07:48,122
We had to move out once
we'd filled the hat with garbage. The end.

115
00:07:54,740 --> 00:07:57,538
Yeah, when those immigrants
get deported...

116
00:07:57,643 --> 00:08:01,238
there'll be a lot more elbowroom
for regular joes like you and me, Apu.

117
00:08:01,347 --> 00:08:03,315
Mr. Simpson...

118
00:08:03,416 --> 00:08:06,385
it may astonish you to learn
that I am an immigrant.

119
00:08:06,486 --> 00:08:09,182
You?
I don't believe it.

120
00:08:09,288 --> 00:08:11,950
No. In truth,
an illegal immigrant, sir.

121
00:08:12,058 --> 00:08:15,619
